-- German State Banks Opposes Publishing Stress Tests as `Counterproductive'
-- Jann Bettinga
-- 2010-06-17T07:18:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/german-state-banks-opposes-publishing-stress-tests-as-counterproductive-.html

          
          
             The Association of German Public
Sector Banks, VOEB, said it’s “clearly against” publishing
results of banks’ stress tests. Publishing them is
“counterproductive” and may lead to misjudgements in the
market, the association said in an e-mailed statement today.  
          
          


  


        